parent.description: Required. The name of the project to which this migration workflow belongs. Example: ``projects/foo/locations/bar``

migration_workflow.description: Required. The migration workflow to create.

name.description: Output only. Immutable. The unique identifier for the migration workflow. The ID is server-generated.  Example: ``projects/123/locations/us/workflows/345``

display_name.description: The display name of the workflow. This can be set to give a workflow a descriptive name. There is no guarantee or enforcement of uniqueness.

tasks.description: The tasks in a workflow in a named map. The name (i.e. key) has no meaning and is merely a convenient way to address a specific task in a workflow.

assessment_task_details.description: Task configuration for Assessment.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``task_details``.

input_path.description: Required. The Cloud Storage path for assessment input files.

output_dataset.description: Required. The BigQuery dataset for output.

querylogs_path.description: Optional. An optional Cloud Storage path to write the query logs (which is then used as an input path on the translation task)

data_source.description: Required. The data source or data warehouse type (eg: TERADATA/REDSHIFT) from which the input data is extracted.

translation_task_details.description: Task configuration for Batch/Offline SQL Translation.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``task_details``.

teradata_options.description: The Teradata SQL specific settings for the translation task.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``language_options``.

bteq_options.description: The BTEQ specific settings for the translation task.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``language_options``.

project_dataset.description: Specifies the project and dataset in BigQuery that will be used for external table creation during the translation.

dataset_id.description: A unique ID for this dataset, without the project name. The ID must contain only letters (a-z, A-Z), numbers (0-9), or underscores (_). The maximum length is 1,024 characters.

project_id.description: The ID of the project containing this dataset.

default_path_uri.description: The Cloud Storage location to be used as the default path for files that are not otherwise specified in the file replacement map.

file_replacement_map.description: Maps the local paths that are used in BTEQ scripts (the keys) to the paths in Cloud Storage that should be used in their stead in the translation (the value).

input_path.description: The Cloud Storage path for translation input files.

output_path.description: The Cloud Storage path for translation output files.

file_paths.description: Cloud Storage files to be processed for translation.

input_path.description: The Cloud Storage path for a file to translation in a subtask.

output_path.description: The Cloud Storage path to write back the corresponding input file to.

schema_path.description: The Cloud Storage path to DDL files as table schema to assist semantic translation.

output_identifier_case.description: The setting to control output queries' identifier case.

identifier_rewrite_mode.description: Specifies the rewrite mode for SQL identifiers.

special_token_map.description: The map capturing special tokens to be replaced during translation. The key is special token in string. The value is the token data type. This is used to translate SQL query template which contains special token as place holder. The special token makes a query invalid to parse. This map will be applied to annotate those special token with types to let parser understand how to parse them into proper structure with type information.

filter.description: The filter applied to translation details.

type_.description: Output only. The full name of the event type (for example, "google.cloud.storage.object.v1.finalized"). In the form of {provider-specific-prefix}.{resource}.{version}.{verb}. Types MUST be versioned and event schemas are guaranteed to remain backward compatible within one version. Note that event type versions and API versions do not need to match.

description.description: Output only. Human friendly description of what the event type is about. For example "Bucket created in Cloud Storage".

filtering_attributes.description: Output only. Filtering attributes for the event type.

attribute.description: Output only. Attribute used for filtering the event type.

description.description: Output only. Description of the purpose of the attribute.

required.description: Output only. If true, the triggers for this provider should always specify a filter on these attributes. Trigger creation will fail otherwise.

path_pattern_supported.description: Output only. If true, the attribute accepts matching expressions in the Eventarc PathPattern format.

event_schema_uri.description: Output only. URI for the event schema. For example "https://github.com/googleapis/google-cloudevents/blob/master/proto/google/events/cloud/storage/v1/events.proto".

translation_exception_table.description: Specifies the exact name of the bigquery table ("dataset.table") to be used for surfacing raw translation errors. If the table does not exist, we will create it. If it already exists and the schema is the same, we will re-use. If the table exists and the schema is different, we will throw an error.

id.description: Output only. Immutable. The unique identifier for the migration task. The ID is server-generated.

type_.description: The type of the task. This must be a supported task type.

details.description: DEPRECATED! Use one of the task_details below. The details of the task. The type URL must be one of the supported task details messages and correspond to the Task's type.

state.description: Output only. The current state of the task.

processing_error.description: Output only. An explanation that may be populated when the task is in FAILED state.

domain.description: The logical grouping to which the "reason" belongs. The error domain is typically the registered service name of the tool or product that generates the error. Example: "pubsub.googleapis.com". If the error is generated by some common infrastructure, the error domain must be a globally unique value that identifies the infrastructure. For Google API infrastructure, the error domain is "googleapis.com".  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``_domain``.

metadatas.description: Additional structured details about this error. Keys must match /a-z+/ but should ideally be lowerCamelCase. Also they must be limited to 64 characters in length. When identifying the current value of an exceeded limit, the units should be contained in the key, not the value. For example, rather than {"instanceLimit": "100/request"}, should be returned as, {"instanceLimitPerRequest": "100"}, if the client exceeds the number of instances that can be created in a single (batch) request.

reason.description: The reason of the error. This is a constant value that identifies the proximate cause of the error. Error reasons are unique within a particular domain of errors. This should be at most 63 characters and match a regular expression of ``A-Z+[A-Z0-9]``, which represents UPPER_SNAKE_CASE.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``_reason``.

create_time.description: Time when the task was created.

last_update_time.description: Time when the task was last updated.

orchestration_result.description: Output only. Additional information about the orchestration.

assessment_details.description: Details specific to assessment task types.  This field is a member of `oneof`_ ``details``.

output_tables_schema_version.description: Optional. The version used for the output table schemas.

state.description: Output only. That status of the workflow.

create_time.description: Time when the workflow was created.

last_update_time.description: Time when the workflow was last updated.
